ed. Fukui function values showed that electrophilic attack of\nHOCl to the C=C bridge in EHMC and MCA is highly favorable (even more\npreferable than phenyl ring chlorination). This suggests that HOCl\nelectrophilic addition is probably the initial step of EHMC degradation.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 29 Apr 2018 12:17:52 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-05-11"}
